buri.ddmsence.ddms.security.ism

Class NoticeAttributes

  • Object
    • buri.ddmsence.AbstractAttributeGroup
      • buri.ddmsence.ddms.security.ism.NoticeAttributes

  • public final class NoticeAttributes
extends AbstractAttributeGroup
    Attribute group for the ISM notice markings used on a Resource and Notice.

    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0

    History

    This class was introduced to support ISM notices in DDMS 4.1. Those components are no longer a part of DDMS 5.0.

    Nested Elements
    NameCardinalityAvailability
    None.
    Attributes
    NameCardinalityAvailability
    ism:noticeType0..1
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    ism:noticeReason0..1
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    ism:noticeDate0..1
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    ism:unregisteredNoticeType0..1
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    ism:externalNotice0..1
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    Validation Rules
    RuleTypeApplicability
    Attribute group must not be used before the DDMS version in which it was introduced.Error
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    If set, ism:noticeType must be a valid token.Error
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    If set, ism:noticeReason must be shorter than 2048 characters.Error
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    If set, ism:unregisteredNoticeType must be shorter than 2048 characters.Error
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0
    If set, ism:noticeDate must adhere to a valid date format.Error
    In DDMS2.03.03.14.0.1/4.15.0

    Does NOT do any validation on the constraints described in the DES ISM specification.

    Since:
    2.0.0

    Brian Uri!
